# 6. Project Testing (ProjectTesting.pdf)

# Project Testing

## Objective

The objective of testing is to verify that the application performs correctly under different input conditions and generates accurate predictions.

---

## Test Environment

Operating System:
Windows 11

IDE:
Visual Studio Code

Programming Language:
Python

Framework:
Flask

---

## Test Cases

### Test Case 1

Input:
Valid Life Expectancy
Valid Schooling
Valid GNI

Expected Result:
Predicted HDI displayed.

Actual Result:
Prediction displayed successfully.

Status:
PASS

---

### Test Case 2

Input:
Missing values

Expected Result:
Validation message shown.

Actual Result:
Input validation works correctly.

Status:
PASS

---

### Test Case 3

Input:
Invalid characters

Expected Result:
Prediction should not proceed.

Actual Result:
Application handles invalid input.

Status:
PASS

---

## Performance Testing

The prediction response is generated within a few seconds.

---

## Result

The application passed all functional tests successfully.

---

## Conclusion

Testing confirmed that the system performs reliably and produces accurate Human Development Index predictions.
